      "writtenOn": "2015-12-09T16:20:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "fyi, direct assignments do not need quoting per Posix, i.e. the line:\n\n   FOO\u003d$BAR\n\nwill always work correctly, even if $BAR contains spaces. On the other hand this is not the case for:\n\n   local FOO\u003d$BAR\n\nthere, the behaviour depends on the shell. Some of them consider \u0027local\u0027 to be a command, and thus this will not work as expected. For others, like bash, \u0027local\u0027 is a keyword and this is still considered a direct assignment. When in doubt, always quote with \u0027local\u0027, but not with direct assignments.\n\nJust mentioning it, the above line is ok.",
      "revId": "904e86e3ba404ed13c53d0618dfe638a4c8bcfad",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
